name: Groups
description: The Groups API is designed for any permanent or semi-permanent collections of Entities (players, or non-players). If you want to make Guilds/Clans/Corporations/etc., then you should use groups. Groups can also be used to make chatrooms, parties, or any other persistent collection of entities.
apiDescriptionList: The Groups API is designed for any permanent or semi-permanent collections of Entities (players, or non-players). If you want to make Guilds/Clans/Corporations/etc., then you should use groups. Groups can also be used to make chatrooms, parties, or any other persistent collection of entities.

AcceptGroupApplicationRequest.name: AcceptGroupApplicationRequest
AcceptGroupApplicationRequest.description: Accepts an outstanding invitation to to join a group if the invited entity is not blocked by the group. Nothing is returned in the case of success.

properties.name: CustomTags
properties.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

properties.name: Entity
properties.description: Optional. Type of the entity to accept as. If specified, must be the same entity as the claimant or an entity that is a child of the claimant entity. Defaults to the claimant entity.

properties.name: Group
properties.description: The identifier of the group

AcceptGroupInvitationRequest.name: AcceptGroupInvitationRequest
AcceptGroupInvitationRequest.description: Accepts an outstanding invitation to join the group if the invited entity is not blocked by the group. Only the invited entity or a parent in its chain (e.g. title) may accept the invitation on the invited entity's behalf. Nothing is returned in the case of success.

properties.name: CustomTags
properties.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

properties.name: Entity
properties.description: The entity to perform this action on.

properties.name: Group
properties.description: The identifier of the group

AddMembersRequest.name: AddMembersRequest
AddMembersRequest.description: Adds members to a group or role. Existing members of the group will added to roles within the group, but if the user is not already a member of the group, only title claimants may add them to the group, and others must use the group application or invite system to add new members to a group. Returns nothing if successful.

properties.name: CustomTags
properties.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

properties.name: Group
properties.description: The identifier of the group

properties.name: Members
properties.description: List of entities to add to the group. Only entities of type title_player_account and character may be added to groups.

properties.name: RoleId
properties.description: Optional: The ID of the existing role to add the entities to. If this is not specified, the default member role for the group will be used. Role IDs must be between 1 and 64 characters long.

ApplyToGroupRequest.name: ApplyToGroupRequest
ApplyToGroupRequest.description: Creates an application to join a group. Calling this while a group application already exists will return the same application instead of an error and will not refresh the time before the application expires. By default, if the entity has an invitation to join the group outstanding, this will accept the invitation to join the group instead and return an error indicating such, rather than creating a duplicate application to join that will need to be cleaned up later. Returns information about the application or an error indicating an invitation was accepted instead.

properties.name: AutoAcceptOutstandingInvite
properties.description: Optional, default true. Automatically accept an outstanding invitation if one exists instead of creating an application

properties.name: CustomTags
properties.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

properties.name: Entity
properties.description: The entity to perform this action on.

properties.name: Group
properties.description: The identifier of the group

ApplyToGroupResponse.name: ApplyToGroupResponse
ApplyToGroupResponse.description: Describes an application to join a group

properties.name: Entity
properties.description: Type of entity that requested membership

properties.name: Expires
properties.description: When the application to join will expire and be deleted

properties.name: Group
properties.description: ID of the group that the entity requesting membership to

BlockEntityRequest.name: BlockEntityRequest
BlockEntityRequest.description: Blocks a list of entities from joining a group. Blocked entities may not create new applications to join, be invited to join, accept an invitation, or have an application accepted. Failure due to being blocked does not clean up existing applications or invitations to the group. No data is returned in the case of success.

properties.name: CustomTags
properties.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

properties.name: Entity
properties.description: The entity to perform this action on.

properties.name: Group
properties.description: The identifier of the group

ChangeMemberRoleRequest.name: ChangeMemberRoleRequest
ChangeMemberRoleRequest.description: Changes the role membership of a list of entities from one role to another in in a single operation. The destination role must already exist. This is equivalent to adding the entities to the destination role and removing from the origin role. Returns nothing if successful.

properties.name: CustomTags
properties.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

properties.name: DestinationRoleId
properties.description: The ID of the role that the entities will become a member of. This must be an existing role. Role IDs must be between 1 and 64 characters long.

properties.name: Group
properties.description: The identifier of the group

properties.name: Members
properties.description: List of entities to move between roles in the group. All entities in this list must be members of the group and origin role.

properties.name: OriginRoleId
properties.description: The ID of the role that the entities currently are a member of. Role IDs must be between 1 and 64 characters long.

CreateGroupRequest.name: CreateGroupRequest
CreateGroupRequest.description: Creates a new group, as well as administration and member roles, based off of a title's group template. Returns information about the group that was created.

properties.name: CustomTags
properties.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

properties.name: Entity
properties.description: The entity to perform this action on.

properties.name: GroupName
properties.description: The name of the group. This is unique at the title level by default.

properties.name: AdminRoleId
properties.description: The ID of the administrator role for the group.

properties.name: Created
properties.description: The server date and time the group was created.

properties.name: Group
properties.description: The identifier of the group

properties.name: GroupName
properties.description: The name of the group.

properties.name: MemberRoleId
properties.description: The ID of the default member role for the group.

properties.name: ProfileVersion
properties.description: The current version of the profile, can be used for concurrency control during updates.

properties.name: Roles
properties.description: The list of roles and names that belong to the group.

CreateGroupRoleRequest.name: CreateGroupRoleRequest
CreateGroupRoleRequest.description: Creates a new role within an existing group, with no members. Both the role ID and role name must be unique within the group, but the name can be the same as the ID. The role ID is set at creation and cannot be changed. Returns information about the role that was created.

properties.name: CustomTags
properties.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

properties.name: Group
properties.description: The identifier of the group

properties.name: RoleId
properties.description: The ID of the role. This must be unique within the group and cannot be changed. Role IDs must be between 1 and 64 characters long.

properties.name: RoleName
properties.description: The name of the role. This must be unique within the group and can be changed later. Role names must be between 1 and 100 characters long

properties.name: ProfileVersion
properties.description: The current version of the group profile, can be used for concurrency control during updates.

properties.name: RoleId
properties.description: ID for the role

properties.name: RoleName
properties.description: The name of the role

DeleteGroupRequest.name: DeleteGroupRequest
DeleteGroupRequest.description: Deletes a group and all roles, invitations, join requests, and blocks associated with it. Permission to delete is only required the group itself to execute this action. The group and data cannot be cannot be recovered once removed, but any abuse reports about the group will remain. No data is returned in the case of success.

properties.name: CustomTags
properties.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

properties.name: Group
properties.description: ID of the group or role to remove

properties.name: CustomTags
properties.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

properties.name: Group
properties.description: The identifier of the group

properties.name: RoleId
properties.description: The ID of the role to delete. Role IDs must be between 1 and 64 characters long.

EntityKey.name: EntityKey
EntityKey.description: Combined entity type and ID structure which uniquely identifies a single entity.

properties.name: Id
properties.description: Unique ID of the entity.

properties.name: Type
properties.description: Entity type. See https://docs.microsoft.com/gaming/playfab/features/data/entities/available-built-in-entity-types

properties.name: TypeString

properties.name: Members

properties.name: RoleId

properties.name: RoleName

EntityWithLineage.name: EntityWithLineage
EntityWithLineage.description: Entity wrapper class that contains the entity key and the entities that make up the lineage of the entity.

properties.name: Key
properties.description: The entity key for the specified entity

properties.name: Lineage
properties.description: Dictionary of entity keys for related entities. Dictionary key is entity type.

GetGroupRequest.name: GetGroupRequest
GetGroupRequest.description: Returns the ID, name, role list and other non-membership related information about a group.

properties.name: CustomTags

properties.name: Group

properties.name: GroupName
properties.description: The full name of the group

properties.name: AdminRoleId
properties.description: The ID of the administrator role for the group.

properties.name: Created

properties.name: Group
properties.description: The identifier of the group

properties.name: GroupName
properties.description: The name of the group.

properties.name: MemberRoleId
properties.description: The ID of the default member role for the group.

properties.name: ProfileVersion
properties.description: The current version of the profile, can be used for concurrency control during updates.

properties.name: Roles
properties.description: The list of roles and names that belong to the group.

GroupApplication.name: GroupApplication
GroupApplication.description: Describes an application to join a group

GroupWithRoles.name: GroupWithRoles
GroupWithRoles.description: Describes a group and the roles that it contains

properties.name: Group
properties.description: ID for the group

properties.name: GroupName
properties.description: The name of the group

properties.name: ProfileVersion
properties.description: The current version of the profile, can be used for concurrency control during updates.

properties.name: Roles

InviteToGroupRequest.name: InviteToGroupRequest
InviteToGroupRequest.description: Invites a player to join a group, if they are not blocked by the group. An optional role can be provided to automatically assign the player to the role if they accept the invitation. By default, if the entity has an application to the group outstanding, this will accept the application instead and return an error indicating such, rather than creating a duplicate invitation to join that will need to be cleaned up later. Returns information about the new invitation or an error indicating an existing application to join was accepted.

properties.name: AutoAcceptOutstandingApplication
properties.description: Optional, default true. Automatically accept an application if one exists instead of creating an invitation

properties.name: CustomTags
properties.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

properties.name: Entity
properties.description: The entity to perform this action on.

properties.name: Group
properties.description: The identifier of the group

properties.name: RoleId
properties.description: Optional. ID of an existing a role in the group to assign the user to. The group's default member role is used if this is not specified. Role IDs must be between 1 and 64 characters long.

InviteToGroupResponse.name: InviteToGroupResponse
InviteToGroupResponse.description: Describes an invitation to a group.

properties.name: Expires
properties.description: When the invitation will expire and be deleted

properties.name: Group
properties.description: The group that the entity invited to

properties.name: InvitedByEntity
properties.description: The entity that created the invitation

properties.name: InvitedEntity
properties.description: The entity that is invited

properties.name: RoleId
properties.description: ID of the role in the group to assign the user to.

IsMemberRequest.name: IsMemberRequest
IsMemberRequest.description: Checks to see if an entity is a member of a group or role within the group. A result indicating if the entity is a member of the group is returned, or a permission error if the caller does not have permission to read the group's member list.

properties.name: CustomTags
properties.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

properties.name: Entity
properties.description: The entity to perform this action on.

properties.name: Group
properties.description: The identifier of the group

properties.name: RoleId
properties.description: Optional: ID of the role to check membership of. Defaults to any role (that is, check to see if the entity is a member of the group in any capacity) if not specified.

properties.name: IsMember
properties.description: A value indicating whether or not the entity is a member.

ListGroupApplicationsRequest.name: ListGroupApplicationsRequest
ListGroupApplicationsRequest.description: Lists all outstanding requests to join a group. Returns a list of all requests to join, as well as when the request will expire. To get the group applications for a specific entity, use ListMembershipOpportunities.

properties.name: CustomTags
properties.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

properties.name: Group
properties.description: The identifier of the group

properties.name: Applications
properties.description: The requested list of applications to the group.

ListGroupBlocksRequest.name: ListGroupBlocksRequest
ListGroupBlocksRequest.description: Lists all entities blocked from joining a group. A list of blocked entities is returned

properties.name: CustomTags
properties.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

properties.name: Group
properties.description: The identifier of the group

properties.name: BlockedEntities
properties.description: The requested list blocked entities.

ListGroupInvitationsRequest.name: ListGroupInvitationsRequest
ListGroupInvitationsRequest.description: Lists all outstanding invitations for a group. Returns a list of entities that have been invited, as well as when the invitation will expire. To get the group invitations for a specific entity, use ListMembershipOpportunities.

properties.name: CustomTags
properties.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

properties.name: Group
properties.description: The identifier of the group

properties.name: Invitations
properties.description: The requested list of group invitations.

ListGroupMembersRequest.name: ListGroupMembersRequest
ListGroupMembersRequest.description: Gets a list of members and the roles they belong to within the group. If the caller does not have permission to view the role, and the member is in no other role, the member is not displayed. Returns a list of entities that are members of the group.

properties.name: CustomTags
properties.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

properties.name: Group
properties.description: ID of the group to list the members and roles for

properties.name: Members
properties.description: The requested list of roles and member entity IDs.

ListMembershipOpportunitiesRequest.name: ListMembershipOpportunitiesRequest
ListMembershipOpportunitiesRequest.description: Lists all outstanding group applications and invitations for an entity. Anyone may call this for any entity, but data will only be returned for the entity or a parent of that entity. To list invitations or applications for a group to check if a player is trying to join, use ListGroupInvitations and ListGroupApplications.

properties.name: CustomTags
properties.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

properties.name: Entity
properties.description: The entity to perform this action on.

properties.name: Applications
properties.description: The requested list of group applications.

properties.name: Invitations
properties.description: The requested list of group invitations.

ListMembershipRequest.name: ListMembershipRequest
ListMembershipRequest.description: Lists the groups and roles that an entity is a part of, checking to see if group and role metadata and memberships should be visible to the caller. If the entity is not in any roles that are visible to the caller, the group is not returned in the results, even if the caller otherwise has permission to see that the entity is a member of that group.

properties.name: CustomTags
properties.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

properties.name: Entity
properties.description: The entity to perform this action on.

properties.name: Groups
properties.description: The list of groups

RemoveGroupApplicationRequest.name: RemoveGroupApplicationRequest
RemoveGroupApplicationRequest.description: Removes an existing application to join the group. This is used for both rejection of an application as well as withdrawing an application. The applying entity or a parent in its chain (e.g. title) may withdraw the application, and any caller with appropriate access in the group may reject an application. No data is returned in the case of success.

properties.name: CustomTags
properties.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

properties.name: Entity
properties.description: The entity to perform this action on.

properties.name: Group
properties.description: The identifier of the group

RemoveGroupInvitationRequest.name: RemoveGroupInvitationRequest
RemoveGroupInvitationRequest.description: Removes an existing invitation to join the group. This is used for both rejection of an invitation as well as rescinding an invitation. The invited entity or a parent in its chain (e.g. title) may reject the invitation by calling this method, and any caller with appropriate access in the group may rescind an invitation. No data is returned in the case of success.

properties.name: CustomTags
properties.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

properties.name: Entity
properties.description: The entity to perform this action on.

properties.name: Group
properties.description: The identifier of the group

RemoveMembersRequest.name: RemoveMembersRequest
RemoveMembersRequest.description: Removes members from a group. A member can always remove themselves from a group, regardless of permissions. Returns nothing if successful.

properties.name: CustomTags
properties.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

properties.name: Group
properties.description: The identifier of the group

properties.name: Members
properties.description: List of entities to remove

properties.name: RoleId
properties.description: The ID of the role to remove the entities from.

UnblockEntityRequest.name: UnblockEntityRequest
UnblockEntityRequest.description: Unblocks a list of entities from joining a group. No data is returned in the case of success.

properties.name: CustomTags
properties.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

properties.name: Entity
properties.description: The entity to perform this action on.

properties.name: Group
properties.description: The identifier of the group

UpdateGroupRequest.name: UpdateGroupRequest
UpdateGroupRequest.description: Updates data about a group, such as the name or default member role. Returns information about whether the update was successful. Only title claimants may modify the administration role for a group.

properties.name: AdminRoleId
properties.description: Optional: the ID of an existing role to set as the new administrator role for the group

properties.name: CustomTags
properties.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

properties.name: ExpectedProfileVersion
properties.description: Optional field used for concurrency control. By specifying the previously returned value of ProfileVersion from the GetGroup API, you can ensure that the group data update will only be performed if the group has not been updated by any other clients since the version you last loaded.

properties.name: Group
properties.description: The identifier of the group

properties.name: GroupName
properties.description: Optional: the new name of the group

properties.name: MemberRoleId
properties.description: Optional: the ID of an existing role to set as the new member role for the group

properties.name: OperationReason
properties.description: Optional reason to explain why the operation was the result that it was.

properties.name: ProfileVersion
properties.description: New version of the group data.

properties.name: SetResult
properties.description: Indicates which operation was completed, either Created, Updated, Deleted or None.

UpdateGroupRoleRequest.name: UpdateGroupRoleRequest
UpdateGroupRoleRequest.description: Updates the role name. Returns information about whether the update was successful.

properties.name: CustomTags
properties.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

properties.name: ExpectedProfileVersion
properties.description: Optional field used for concurrency control. By specifying the previously returned value of ProfileVersion from the GetGroup API, you can ensure that the group data update will only be performed if the group has not been updated by any other clients since the version you last loaded.

properties.name: Group
properties.description: The identifier of the group

properties.name: RoleId
properties.description: ID of the role to update. Role IDs must be between 1 and 64 characters long.

properties.name: RoleName
properties.description: The new name of the role

properties.name: OperationReason
properties.description: Optional reason to explain why the operation was the result that it was.

properties.name: ProfileVersion
properties.description: New version of the role data.

properties.name: SetResult
properties.description: Indicates which operation was completed, either Created, Updated, Deleted or None.

calls.name: UnblockEntity
calls.summary: Unblocks a list of entities from joining a group
calls.requestDetails: Unblocks a list of entities from joining a group. No data is returned in the case of success.

calls.name: UpdateGroup
calls.summary: Updates non-membership data about a group.
calls.requestDetails: Updates data about a group, such as the name or default member role. Returns information about whether the update was successful. Only title claimants may modify the administration role for a group.

calls.name: UpdateRole
calls.summary: Updates metadata about a role.
calls.requestDetails: Updates the role name. Returns information about whether the update was successful.
